-- Police in Berlin, Dresden Arrest Five in Probe of People-Smuggling Group
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-06-22T10:16:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/police-in-berlin-dresden-arrest-five-in-probe-of-people-smuggling-group.html

          
          
             Police in Berlin and Dresden,
Germany arrested a total of five people today as part of a probe
into an alleged Vietnamese people-smuggling ring. The
investigation also involved “measures” in France and Hungary,
a joint statement by the Berlin police, the city’s prosecutors
office and the German federal police said.  
 The ring allegedly smuggled 60 Vietnamese people through
the Czech Republic and into Germany, then on to France and
Britain, the statement said.  
          
          


  


        